epic /ˈɛpɪk/

(epics) 

1. N-COUNT An epic is a long book, poem, or film whose story extends over a long period of time or tells of great events. 史诗; 史诗般的作品 

例： ...the Middle High German epic, 'Nibelungenlied,' written about 

1200. …大约写于1200年的中古高地德语史诗《尼贝龙根之歌》。 

2. ADJ Epic is also an adjective. 史诗般的 

例： ...epic narrative poems. …那些史诗般的叙事诗。 

3. ADJ Something that is epic is very large and impressive. 伟大的; 宏大的 

例： ...Columbus's epic voyage of discovery. …哥伦布的伟大发现之旅。

